<TITLE> Govt seeks UNFPA help for flood-affected pregnant women </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 15 (bdnews24.com) -- The government Wednesday requested the UNFPA to provide medicines and logistic support for Bangladesh to take care of 60,000 expectant mothers, affected by floods. "At least 60,000 expectant mothers have been affected by the recent floods. I have requested the UNFPA to provide necessary medicines and logistic support for them," foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury told reporters in his office after his meeting with the UNFPA chief for Bangladesh. UNFPA country director Arthur Erkan met the adviser and informed him that at least 60,000 expectant mothers had been affected by the floods. Chinese embassy officials in Dhaka donated Tk 10.1 lakh in aid to flood-hit people in Bangladesh. Chinese ambassador to Bangladesh Zheng Qingdian met Iftekhar at the foreign ministry and handed over the cheque for funds. "I hope the people of Bangladesh will be able to defeat floods," Zheng Qingdain told reporters. "The ambassador and I have discussed ways to determine how China can help us fight floods," the adviser told bdews24.com. bdn
